# Design Handoff (Claude Design ↔ this project)

## What is Claude Design (read first if unfamiliar)

`Claude Design` is Anthropic's web app at `https://claude.ai/design` that
generates UI mockups and interactive prototypes from text prompts. It
launched April 2026 and requires a paid Claude account (Pro / Max / Team /
Enterprise). It exports bundles in two formats:

- **Handoff to Claude Code…** (preferred) — structured `.zip` containing
  `manifest.json`, `spec.json`, `design-tokens.json`, `README.md`,
  `components/`, `assets/`. Machine-readable; the bridge ingest tool
  validates it.
- **Download project as .zip** — raw React code only (`*.html` + `*.jsx`).
  Use only if the structured option is unavailable; the import skill has
  a documented fallback path for this case.

There is **no native "Send to Cursor" button**. The bridge fills that gap
by driving the browser via the `cursor-ide-browser` MCP and auto-ingesting
the export. Both skills referenced below contain Background sections with
concrete UI element names (snapshot refs, button labels) for agents
without prior product knowledge.

## When to load which skill

| Trigger | Skill to follow |
|---|---|
| User invokes `/claude-design` or asks to "generate a design via browser" | `.cursor/skills/claude-design-browser/SKILL.md` |
| User provides a `.zip`, a `.design/handoff/<slug>/` directory, or a `claude.ai/design/...` share URL | `.cursor/skills/import-claude-design/SKILL.md` |
| User invokes `/import-claude-design` | same as above |

## Hard rules

- Do not improvise. Read the relevant skill end-to-end before acting.
- Always reconcile `design-tokens.json` against `src/index.css` before
  generating components.
- Always reuse existing components in `src/components/` over generating
  new ones.
- Never copy raw hex colors from the bundle into components — go through
  the project's token layer.
- Never invent backend endpoints to satisfy a spec. If the spec references
  an endpoint that does not exist, stop and surface the gap.

The supported flow is:

```
/claude-design  →  browser MCP drives claude.ai/design  →  Export .zip
       │                                                      │
       └──────────  scripts/ingest-claude-design.mjs  ────────┘
                                  │
                  /import-claude-design (or auto handoff)
                                  │
              implement against this project's frontend
```

For the reverse direction (project → Claude Design), do not build a custom
uploader. Use Claude Design's "Web capture" against the running dev server,
or the Figma MCP if a designer is in the loop.
